### Get My Profile - GET request (Local Testing)
# Simula Easy Auth in locale usando gli header X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-*
# X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-ID = sub/oid claim (GUID dell'utente)
# X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-NAME = email/preferred_username claim
GET http://localhost:7047/api/profiles/me
X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-ID: 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-NAME: test@example.com

###

### Create or Update Profile - POST request (Local Testing)
POST http://localhost:7071/api/profiles
X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-ID: 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-NAME: test@example.com
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "TestUser",
  "bio": "Questa è la mia biografia di test"
}

###

### Upload Profile Image - POST request (Local Testing)
POST http://localhost:7071/api/profiles/image
X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-ID: 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-NAME: test@example.com
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< C:/Users/viezzi/Pictures/avatar.jpg

###

### Get My Profile - GET request (Production with Easy Auth)
# In produzione, invia il token JWT nell'header Authorization
# Easy Auth lo valida e popola automaticamente gli header X-MS-CLIENT-PRINCIPAL-*
GET https://your-function-app.azurewebsites.net/api/profiles/me
Authorization: Bearer {actual-jwt-token}

###

### Create or Update Profile - POST request (Production with Easy Auth)
POST https://your-function-app.azurewebsites.net/api/profiles
Authorization: Bearer {actual-jwt-token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "TestUser",
  "bio": "Questa è la mia biografia di test"
}

